Biography

Career Highlights

• A two-time member of the Detroit Mercy Athletic Director's Honor Roll.

• Played in 35 career matches (25 starts) in the red, white and blue.

2020 (Played in spring 2021)

• Played in eight matches, making six starts.

• Earned playing time in 508 minutes for the Titans on defense.

• Played all 110 minutes in a 0-0 draw with IUPUI (2/24).

• Earned Detroit Mercy Athletic Director's Honor Roll (3.0 GPA+) accolades.

2019

• Saw action in 14 games with 13 starts.

• Had two total shots and totaled 1,082 minutes of playing time on the back line, which ranked fifth on the squad.

• Posted a shot at Purdue Fort Wayne and against IUPUI.

• Earned Detroit Mercy Athletic Director's Honor Roll (3.0 GPA+) accolades.

2018

• Played in three games and made one start before an injury ended her season.

• Started at defense in the season opener at Western Michigan.

2017

• Appeared in 10 games with five starts and totaled 600 minutes.

• Attempted three shots on the season, all in Horizon League play.

• Made her collegiate debut at Fort Wayne and her first collegiate start at Northern Arizona.

High School

• Multi-sport athlete with letters in soccer, flag football, volleyball and basketball for the Riverhawks.

• In soccer, team won the Hershey Centre Tournament Championship in 2015 and the Tournament of Champions in 2016.

• Also won championships in basketball and flag football.

• Played 12 years with the Brams United Girls Soccer Club.

• Club team was SRSL League Champions and Cup Champions in 2014, Indoor Ontario Cup Champions in 2013, Robbie Tournament Finalists in 2012 and 2013 and Disney Memorial Day Tournament Champions in 2012.

• Named Oshawa Kicks Tournament MVP in 2014 and was a captain for three years.

Personal

• Daughter of Tarin Neil and Bernard Tavernier.

• Has one sibling, Kevaughn.

• Major is Architecture.

No stats available for the current season.
